<br>
Good because it helps stores like Gallop's, and cuts down on the internet sales sites that really only exist as a store on paper from selling at just above cost.  There is a reason that WoTC and WizKids are also doing this, its because these actions hurt the business and hobby overall.  GW is in the business to make money, and one way of doing that is by expanding the hobby, which involves game communities and physical stores.<br>
<br>
It's bad because they are doing this just on the heels of price hike in a shaky consumer economy.  Everyone is complaining about the high prices of GW products compared to other companies, this is only going to make GW seem like the RIAA of the miniature company to the eyes of many customers. <br>
<br>
Two message boards I've already looked at today have been split between the good part I described above or a 'down with GW' spirit.  <br>
<br>
They could have planned this better, I don't really question their pricing on models as much as I do on their printed books that are rules / fluff compendiums from WD.<br>
