<br>
--------------------------------<br>
I own The Gamer's Realm in NJ, and I spoke with someone high up in GW earlier regarding this.<br>
<br>
This is an IP issue for them. What that means to them is that without specific written permission to use their IP's, i.e. marketting, advertisements, etc., we are not allowed to sell GW products on the Internet.<br>
<br>
While this does include E-Bay Auction Stores and the like (half.com. Amazon affiliates, etc.) it does not preclude individuals from selling thir personal products online. However, as many of us know, many stores do sell via auction on E-Bay and other auction sites. If they can prove that these are stores &amp; businesses, rather than individual persons, then they will ask to cease and desist. It is not that hard to prove, either.<br>
<br>
Rob Placer - Owner<br>
The Gamer's Realm, Inc.<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Also chatting with the guys at thewarstore, they will still be able to see, but only with phone calls  and faxes (after you set up an account with them), but no internet sales.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thewarstore.com/acatalog/info_INQ1.html" target="top">This</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is one of thier old links.  An obivious use of the IP to sell thier product.  This is not showing hte cover of a book or a box, but painted models by the 'Eavy Metal team.<br>
<br>
The more i think about it and listen to intellegent people, the more this sounds like an IP debate not a &quot;we will stop selling on the internet&quot; debate.  <br>
<br>
